title: Mosob
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Eritrean cuisine in a setting that reflects the country's culture, with original art and artifacts. Eritrean and Ethiopian fasting food is vegan, so there is a variety of vegan/vegetarian food on the menu, including vegetable served on top of flattened pancake-like bread, called injera, with extra injera on the side. You eat your meal with your hands.
